    		<article class="post-2757 page type-page status-publish hentry" id="post-2757"><h2><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/covid-19/">COVID-19</a></h2>

				<div class="entry">

					<h2>BATESVILLE COMMUNITY SCHOOL CORPORATION COVID-19 AND ELEARNING INFORMATION</h2>
<div style="padding: 20px;border-left: solid 4px #017CC6;background-color: #f1f1f1;margin-top: 10px;font-weight: bold">
<p>IT Support will be available on April 27th from 8-11 am for hardware related issues that require a loaner computer.</p>
<p>For Tech Issues, please call 812-932-4060 and leave a message or email <a href="mailto:helpdesk@batesville.k12.in.us">helpdesk@batesville.k12.in.us</a></p>
</div>
<p><strong>Information regarding school closure through the end of the academic year due to the COVID-19 pandemic.</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/COVID-19-Closure.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Closure Letter</a><br><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/BCSC-Parent-COVID-19-Letter.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC Parent COVID 19 Letter</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Mr. Ketcham Daily COVID-19 Update</strong></p>
<p>Daily videos to communicate important information as we progress through this enormous challenge.</p>
<p>DAY #11: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1qh5s1CcdbunCJON-voFZyNY_S9_Lxk4c/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 11</a><br>
DAY #10: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1v05Wtdc31COQJZ3bZKWHfwZ5zZjM15ex/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 10</a><br>
DAY #9: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NHbk1PdMkyvnuTOfPEd8kNvRwrWOaXaO/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 9</a><br>
DAY #8: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ucLlAXMUY6ht6_Rvana81FT81n-FyJjR/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 8</a><br>
DAY #7: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/15VPWV6tCNR50Rr_cfsWQ4Mxd6XEFcfls/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 7</a><br>
DAY #6: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/13oOB0XaPPo-5R_U870zZdGBXVgNUetmG/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 6</a><br>
DAY #5: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l5EcLBuuINnky3Indu0KLpZ-BFB4Pa_Z/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 5</a><br>
DAY #4: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1FYGLLQNMNeMLJymFaceRZVGtqz4ZrXFn/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 4</a><br>
DAY #3: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Odz2SiY_sK3_FcY4-rak83-nqX2mDmZy/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 3</a><br>
DAY #2: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-0ETy-23AfO6TIXyo8y4sE5XdQsIMuuU/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update 2</a><br>
DAY #1: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1TWBuOUITat8-NfTZ98YaiMItAF7pq4G7/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCSC COVID-19 Daily Update</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>School Calendar Information</strong></p>
<p>BCSC will be utilizing five (5) COVID-19 waiver days for the week of March 30 – April 3. COVID-19 waiver days equate to no school for our students, teachers and support staff will be ramping up to provide eLearning instruction the week of April 6.</p>
<p><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Calendar-2019-2020-REV-4_6_20b.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Revised School Calendar</a><br><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/eLearning-Calendar-2019-2020.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">April eLearning Calendar</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>eLearning Frequently Asked Questions / Parent Canvas Resources</strong><br><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/BCSC-eLearning-FAQ-4-20-1.pdf">BCSC eLearning FAQ April 2020</a><br><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/BCSC-Canvas-parent-19.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Canvas Parent Account</a><br><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/eLearning-Canvas-Parent-BHS.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Parent Technology Tools</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Food Service Information</strong></p>
<p>BCSC is continuing to provide meals for all students during this period of school closure. These meals are free. A week’s worth of breakfasts and lunches will be provided each Monday. The link to sign up will be open from 8:00am Tuesday to 6:00pm Thursday. Please sign up by Thursday at 6:00pm each week for meals for the following week. You must sign up weekly for meals by clicking the following link: <a href="https://forms.gle/Kpta2zczjxreKcGv8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://forms.gle/Kpta2zczjxreKcGv8</a></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pick-up location: Batesville Intermediate School</strong></li>
<li><strong><u>MONDAYS ONLY from 10:30-12:30</u></strong></li>
<li><strong>Includes 5 breakfasts and 5 lunches per child (meals include frozen, cold, and shelf stable food)</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>While you should always take precaution when venturing out, please know that we are following every safety protocol and best practices for social distancing at meal sites to combat the spread of disease. All meals are served in a grab and go format, with drive through pickup, to limit social interactions. Drive through pickup is an easy process:</p>
<ol>
<li>Pull up to the designated location</li>
<li>Roll down your window and tell the nutrition staff how many meals you need</li>
<li>Staff will place the number of meals you requested on a cart and step back</li>
<li>You will exit your car and grab your meals</li>
</ol>
<p><em>We do have delivery available if necessary. You can indicate the need for delivery when you sign up with the link above. Meals will be delivered each Monday between the hours of 10:30 and noon.</em></p>
<p>Any questions can be directed to Berna Meyer, Director of Food Services, at <a href="mailto:bmeyer@batesville.k12.in.us">bmeyer@batesville.k12.in.us</a>.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Parent information from the Indiana Department of Education (IDOE)</strong></p>
<p>The cancellation of the upcoming Spring 2020 assessment windows.<br><a href="https://batesvilleinschools.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Parent-COVID-19-Spring-Testing-Decision.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Parent COVID-19 Spring Testing Decision</a></p>
<p>COVID-19 Family Resources<br><a href="https://www.doe.in.gov/elearning/2020-covid-19-remote-learning?utm_content=&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_name=&amp;utm_source=govdelivery&amp;utm_term=#family%20resources" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Indiana Department of Education – 2020 COVID-19 Remote Learning Family Resources</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Contact Information:<br><span style="font-size: 10pt">For assistance, please contact the following:</span><br></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Tech Issues – Call 812-932-4060 and leave a message or email <a href="mailto:helpdesk@batesville.k12.in.us">helpdesk@batesville.k12.in.us</a>
</li>
<li>Canvas – email Jackie Huber – <a href="mailto:jhuber@batesville.k12.in.us">jhuber@batesville.k12.in.us</a>
